on different branches,

00:05:40.730 --> 00:05:43.110
and then tried to merge
it back into master scene,

00:05:43.110 --> 00:05:45.480
people's changes were
lost or overwritten.

00:05:45.480 --> 00:05:48.089
So we found that Unity
wasn't great in terms

00:05:48.089 --> 00:05:50.380
of like having a big team
project where a lot of people

00:05:50.380 --> 00:05:51.180
are coding at once.

00:05:51.180 --> 00:05:54.170
And sometimes we just
re-applied changes

00:05:54.170 --> 00:05:56.496
on to the master branch.

00:05:56.496 --> 00:05:58.730
Something else was we all
had really busy schedules.

00:05:58.730 --> 00:06:00.150
People were out of town.

00:06:00.150 --> 00:06:03.205
In town, they could only work on
the project at certain points.

00:06:03.205 --> 00:06:07.450
So I think something that helped
with that was at the beginning,

00:06:07.450 --> 00:06:10.880
we did a pretty good job of
delegating tasks to people who

00:06:10.880 --> 00:06:12.520
work on the project earlier.

00:06:12.520 --> 00:06:14.910
But then later on
it, it was pretty

00:06:14.910 --> 00:06:17.160
haphazard in terms of who
is available at one of time.

00:06:17.160 --> 00:06:20.510
So maybe re-evaluating
priorities

00:06:20.510 --> 00:06:25.366
as the project went on would've,
I think, really helpful.

