00:17:02.370 --> 00:17:05.057
So what went right
in our project?

00:17:05.057 --> 00:17:06.640
I think what went
right in our project

00:17:06.640 --> 00:17:09.729
is we connected
with our audience.

00:17:12.520 --> 00:17:15.980
A lot of MIT students know
what it's like to be at MIT,

00:17:15.980 --> 00:17:19.150
and they know the
setting, they knew

00:17:19.150 --> 00:17:22.240
the administrator We're
not really pointing at,

00:17:22.240 --> 00:17:23.390
but we kind of are.

00:17:23.390 --> 00:17:26.770
And so a lot of people connected
very well with our game.

00:17:26.770 --> 00:17:32.480
And so they enjoyed it and were
able to understand it easily

00:17:32.480 --> 00:17:34.530
in their own terms.

00:17:34.530 --> 00:17:40.470
So the second thing that went
well is that humor works.

00:17:40.470 --> 00:17:44.480
A lot of our things in our game
were like kind of unpolished,

00:17:44.480 --> 00:17:46.510
and kind of like
slapped together.

00:17:46.510 --> 00:17:49.440
But because we had taken
the time to make them funny

00:17:49.440 --> 00:17:51.640
and make them
