really useful to have somebody

00:32:35.450 --> 00:32:36.550
say like,

00:32:36.550 --> 00:32:38.440
OK, this is what
everybody's done.

00:32:38.440 --> 00:32:40.150
This is what
everybody's going to do.

00:32:40.150 --> 00:32:41.620
This is what we've submitted.

00:32:41.620 --> 00:32:46.150
Having that one thing somewhere
where everyone can view it

00:32:46.150 --> 00:32:48.200
easily would make
it a lot easier

00:32:48.200 --> 00:32:51.560
than trying to go through email
and figuring out who did what

00:32:51.560 --> 00:32:54.374
and what went wrong.

00:32:54.374 --> 00:32:56.790
One other thing we did right
was we went in smaller group.

00:32:56.790 --> 00:33:00.800
So people were working on the
design, just those people met.

00:33:00.800 --> 00:33:03.190
And then people working on
the code, just those people

00:33:03.190 --> 00:33:06.860
met, which was really
useful for trying to meet.

00:33:06.860 --> 00:33:08.690
Instead of having
seven people meet,

00:33:08.690 --> 00:33:10.170
you only had like three or four.

00:33:10.170 --> 00:33:13.060
And so much easier to
arrange those meetings.

00:33:13.060 --> 00:33:15.560
We really divided the
tasks effectively.

00:33:15.560 --> 00:33:18.160
Everybody was doing something.

00:33:18.160 --> 00:33:20.915
And that's what
the last point is.

00:33:20.915 --> 00:33:22.950
Everybody tried to make
sure they were always

00:33:22.950 --> 00:33:24.950
doing something and
contributing to the project.

00:33:24.950 --> 00:33:28.170
No one was just sitting there
wondering, what do I do.

00:33:28.170 --> 00:33:30.775
Everyone tried to constantly
be doing something.

00:33:34.450 --> 00:33:38.510
Another thing that went wrong
is that we worked in bursts.

00:33:38.510 --> 00:33:39.620
People were really busy.

00:33:39.620 --> 00:33:42.970
And then the night before we
assigned an internal deadline,

00:33:42.970 --> 00:33:45.620
