have a paper prototype.

00:41:02.620 --> 00:41:05.030
We had an idea that
we wanted to do.

00:41:05.030 --> 00:41:09.180
But it ended up changing a
lot right from the start.

00:41:09.180 --> 00:41:12.480
And it became really
difficult to stay on topic

00:41:12.480 --> 00:41:15.470
because we didn't really
know what we were doing.

00:41:15.470 --> 00:41:19.170
And very much related to that,
we then had issues with scope.

00:41:19.170 --> 00:41:22.320
We started off with a
lot of unrelated features

00:41:22.320 --> 00:41:23.730
and a lot of components.

00:41:23.730 --> 00:41:27.340
And even now in our final game,
there are a lot of components

00:41:27.340 --> 00:41:31.960
and the way they interact
is complicated sometimes.

00:41:31.960 --> 00:41:34.860
And then finally, I think every
single team has mentioned this,

00:41:34.860 --> 00:41:37.980
just planning ahead, and
getting work done earlier,

00:41:37.980 --> 00:41:40.930
and planning time to work
together-- the issues we had

00:41:40.930 --> 00:41:43.200
especially that came up
later were a lot of issues

00:41:43.200 --> 00:41:46.490
with midterms,
things going wrong,

00:41:46.490 --> 00:41:49.310
everything that could go
wrong kind of went wrong.

00:41:49.310 --> 00:41:51.710
And if we had
started earlier, we

00:41:51.710 --> 00:41:53.240
wouldn't have
had-- we would have

00:41:53.240 --> 00:41:56.760
been able to deal with
those situations better.

00:41:56.760 --> 00:41:59.210
