up everything we needed to work.

00:42:04.160 --> 00:42:07.410
We set up our email thread,
our Google Drive folder.

00:42:07.410 --> 00:42:09.370
We decided on Unity
first meeting,

00:42:09.370 --> 00:42:12.120
and we set up the GitHub
project right away so

00:42:12.120 --> 00:42:13.560
that we could all collaborate.

00:42:13.560 --> 00:42:15.310
And the nice thing was
in our Google Drive

00:42:15.310 --> 00:42:16.970
folder we put our task list.

00:42:16.970 --> 00:42:19.105
We really utilized that.

00:42:19.105 --> 00:42:20.950
And our email thread,
like other teams said,

00:42:20.950 --> 00:42:22.610
it did get a little
long and complex.

00:42:22.610 --> 00:42:24.370
But it was just so nice to have.

00:42:24.370 --> 00:42:27.110
And later on, we actually
also got a group text

00:42:27.110 --> 00:42:28.330
messaging service.

00:42:28.330 --> 00:42:32.160
So that works really well
dealing with that last minute

00:42:32.160 --> 00:42:34.230
hustle kind of stuff.

00:42:34.230 --> 00:42:36.010
The next thing I
went really well

00:42:36.010 --> 00:42:39.590
is I told you that our
scope was way out there.

00:42:39.590 --> 00:42:41.980
We realized that very
quickly, and we just

00:42:41.980 --> 00:42:43.860
started cutting,
cutting, cutting.

00:42:43.860 --> 00:42:44.980
So we cut items.

00:42:44.980 --> 00:42:47.560
We cut interactive
AI characters.

00:42:47.560 --> 00:42:49.490
We cut playable quizzes.

00:42:49.490 --> 00:42:52.680
We just cut everything
that wasn't key.

00:42:52.680 --> 00:42:54.970
Because our game, even
without all the things,

00:42:54.970 --> 00:42:56.610
already had a lot of components.

00:42:59.350 --> 00:43:03.060
And then once we have a playable
game, the next thing we did

00:43:03.060 --> 00:43:04.780
was we looked into feedback.

00:43:04.780 --> 00:43:08.640
So one of the main feedbacks
we got was our game

00:43:08.640 --> 00:43:10.400
was not visually cohesive.

00:43:10.400 --> 00:43:11.850
It did not make sense.

00:43:11.850 --> 00:43:13.930
The nice thing
about Score High was

00:43:13.930 --> 00:43:16.020
that because you're
playing as an MIT student,

00:43:16.020 --> 00:43:19.060
you're just getting work done,
people understood how to play

00:43:19.060 --> 00:43:20.700
and what they were
supposed to do.

00:43:20.700 --> 00:43:22.304
But they didn't understand that.

00:43:22.304 --> 00:43:23.970
So if you look at the
thing on the left,

00:43:23.970 --> 00:43:26.940
you're probably all just staring
at it being like, what's that.

00:43:26.940 --> 00:43:29.180
The rectangles are
buildings, and the bottom's

00:43:29.180 --> 00:43:31.190
the stats bar, on the
right is the schedule.

00:43:31.190 --> 00:43:32.230
It's confusing.

00:43:32.230 --> 00:43:33.801
People didn't notice
the stat bars,

00:43:33.801 --> 00:43:35.300
or they thought
they were buildings,

00:43:35.300 --> 00:43:36.550
and things like that.

00:43:36.550 --> 00:43:38.130
So we responded to
that right away.

00:43:38.130 --> 00:43:39.750
And we said, we need
to clarify this.

00:43:39.750 --> 00:43:43.510
We need to separate the
status, separate the schedule,

00:43:43.510 --> 00:43:49.410
and make the map very clear, and
pretty, and easy to get around.

00:43:49.410 --> 00:43:51.390
So that was one thing
we responded to,

00:43:51.390 --> 00:43:52.960
and I think it went well.

00:43:52.960 --> 00:43:55.010
The next thing that we
responded to feedback

00:43:55.010 --> 00:43:57.960
was we really listened to
players, not only big picture,

00:43:57.960 --> 00:43:59.280
but on smaller things.

00:43:59.280 --> 00:44:02.990
Players wanted WASD,
so we put WASD.

00:44:02.990 --> 00:44:05.370
They wanted a clear
way to leave buildings.

00:44:05.370 --> 00:44:07.120
They wanted to know
what was going on when

00:44:07.120 --> 00:44:08.200
they were in a building.

00:44:08.200 --> 00:44:11.510
So we actually inserted
a progress bar that says,

00:44:11.510 --> 00:44:14.080
what's going on this building,
how it's affecting you.

00:44:14.080 --> 00:44:15.950
And then to leave,
instead of pressing

00:44:15.950 --> 00:44:18.730
space bar, which people
found unintuitive,

00:44:18.730 --> 00:44:21.560
they press a button that says
leave-- much more intuitive.

00:44:24.660 --> 00:44:26.971
Now given all that, we did
make a really good game.

00:44:26.971 --> 00:44:28.470
But there are
definitely some things

00:44:28.470 --> 00:44:31.290
