01:36:58.900 --> 01:37:04.390
The humanitarian sector has
two main funding mechanisms.

01:37:04.390 --> 01:37:07.640
Imagine a pot of money.

01:37:07.640 --> 01:37:11.950
Even if there's almost no
money there, if the pot exists,

01:37:11.950 --> 01:37:15.990
money can go in, to then
be taken out to spend.

01:37:15.990 --> 01:37:18.750
One of the pots of money that
exists, one of the funding

01:37:18.750 --> 01:37:22.790
mechanisms that exists
is for disaster response,

01:37:22.790 --> 01:37:26.150
meaning a hurricane,
flood, volcanic eruption.

01:37:26.150 --> 01:37:30.230
Something has already
happened, is happening,

01:37:30.230 --> 01:37:32.490
and is killing people.

01:37:32.490 --> 01:37:35.100
People are dying, but
if you did something,

01:37:35.100 --> 01:37:36.690
you could save lives.

01:37:36.690 --> 01:37:39.040
For example, get on a
boat and rescue people

01:37:39.040 --> 01:37:41.670
who are stranded on a roof.

01:37:41.670 --> 01:37:42.550
Or people are sick.

01:37:42.550 --> 01:37:44.590
Go give them medicine.

01:37:44.590 --> 01:37:45.860
This is disaster response.

01:37:45.860 --> 01:37:49.350
And if you spend money, you
can do very good things.

01:37:49.350 --> 01:37:51.627
And the funding
mechanism exists.

01:37:51.627 --> 01:37:55.220
There is another pot of money
which is for a normal days.

01:37:55.220 --> 01:37:56.510
The Red Cross has vehicles.

01:37:56.510 --> 01:37:58.030
The vehicles needs maintenance.

01:37:58.030 --> 01:37:59.450
They need to change tires.

01:37:59.450 --> 01:38:01.360
You need to buy a new computer.

01:38:01.360 --> 01:38:04.860
You need to pay rent and
the electricity bills.

01:38:04.860 --> 01:38:06.860
You need to train staff.

01:38:06.860 --> 01:38:11.036
So on a normal day, you have a
budget for either maintenance,

01:38:11.036 --> 01:38:14.185
or development of new
projects, or writing proposals,

01:38:14.185 --> 01:38:15.330
and so on.

01:38:15.330 --> 01:38:17.090
And when that pot
of money exists,

01:38:17.090 --> 01:38:19.770
we called it the annual appeal.

01:38:19.770 --> 01:38:22.340
Every year, we appeal for help.

01:38:22.340 --> 01:38:27.430
And people or donors, or
governments give us some money.

01:38:27.430 --> 01:38:31.240
What does not exists is what
the drawing of the cartoon

01:38:31.240 --> 01:38:35.750
depicts, which is when there
is a signal from science

01:38:35.750 --> 01:38:41.640
that a disasters, that something
bad is likely to happen soon.

01:38:41.640 --> 01:38:46.770
We don't have money to fund
action before the disaster,

01:38:46.770 --> 01:38:49.060
after the forecast.

01:38:49.060 --> 01:38:52.650
So if you click to see
the text, the context

01:38:52.650 --> 01:38:55.200
is that there that
missing money part.

01:38:55.200 --> 01:38:56.930
We have money for
after a disaster,

01:38:56.930 --> 01:38:58.640
we have money for
everyone all day.

01:38:58.640 --> 01:39:00.745
But we don't have money
for before the disaster,

01:39:00.745 --> 01:39:02.420
after the forecast.

01:39:02.420 --> 01:39:06.390
The issue is that if you spend
money in that time window,

01:39:06.390 --> 01:39:08.500
before the disaster
and after the scientist

01:39:08.500 --> 01:39:10.490
says a disaster
is likely, you can

01:39:10.490 --> 01:39:14.530
do very good things for
very cheap, and relatively

01:39:14.530 --> 01:39:16.330
simply, and much more reliably.

01:39:16.330 --> 01:39:18.380
It's not only more
expensive, but more

01:39:18.380 --> 01:39:23.080
difficult to save a life when
the storm waters are flashing

01:39:23.080 --> 01:39:26.180
through a city and people
are above the ground.

01:39:26.180 --> 01:39:27.910
The boat is unstable.

01:39:27.910 --> 01:39:30.690
Whereas if you do
it the day before,

01:39:30.690 --> 01:39:33.220
when the water has
come down from the sky

01:39:33.220 --> 01:39:36.250
but it's still in the
river and not in the city,

01:39:36.250 --> 01:39:39.110
people can take action
by just walking away,

01:39:39.110 --> 01:39:42.080
on your own means,
with your valuables

01:39:42.080 --> 01:39:45.370
and not just depending on
someone to show up with a boat.

01:39:45.370 --> 01:39:47.870
So we came up with a
financial mechanism,

01:39:47.870 --> 01:39:49.870
we call it
forecast-based financing

01:39:49.870 --> 01:39:54.020
for disaster preparedness
which is nuanced

01:39:54.020 --> 01:39:55.230
in how it's implemented.

01:39:55.230 --> 01:39:56.410
There is a pot of money.

01:39:56.410 --> 01:39:57.780
It's like a bank account.

01:39:57.780 --> 01:40:01.705
You need to have a
threshold of disaster risk

01:40:01.705 --> 01:40:03.390
that needs to be exceeded.

01:40:03.390 --> 01:40:05.390
So it can not be
two drops of rain.

01:40:05.390 --> 01:40:06.690
It has to be a lot of rain.

01:40:06.690 --> 01:40:08.010
It can not be some wind.

01:40:08.010 --> 01:40:10.710
It has to be a hurricane
category 1 or more.

01:40:10.710 --> 01:40:12.955
But once the threshold is
established and reached

01:40:12.955 --> 01:40:15.760
by the forecast, then there's
some standard operating

01:40:15.760 --> 01:40:19.450
procedures, some actions
that people have to take,

01:40:19.450 --> 01:40:22.300
spending money to save lives.

01:40:22.300 --> 01:40:24.810
And that is something
that if you could come up

01:40:24.810 --> 01:40:31.260
with a game that captures that,
this is the one that if we help

01:40:31.260 --> 01:40:33.470
